<tool id="ChangeCase1" name="Change Case">
  <description>to upper or lower</description>
  <command interpreter="perl">changeCase.pl $input $out_file1 "$upperLower"</command>
  <inputs>
    <param format="txt" name="input" type="data" label="Change"/>
    <param name="upperLower" type="select" label="To">
      <option value="up">Upper case</option>
      <option value="lo">Lower case</option>
    </param>
  </inputs>
  <outputs>
    <data format="tabular" name="out_file1" />
  </outputs>
  <tests>
    <test>
      <param name="input" value="1.txt"/>
      <param name="upperLower" value="up"/>
      <output name="out_file1" file="change-case.dat"/>
    </test>
  </tests>
  <help>

This tool changes case for lower to upper and vice versa.  

.. class:: infomark

If you want to change case on a specific column use this tool in combination with *Text Manipulation->Cut*

</help>
</tool>
